    "recap_headline": "Rice University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "TAMPA, Fla. \u2014 Rice's\nBrayden Sharp\nstruck out 11 in relief, but South Florida got a first inning run, and Michael Senay made it hold up, as USF evened the series, 2-0, Saturday afternoon.\nSouth Florida (19-4, 1-1) grabbed the lead in the first inning. After the first two batters reached, Nathan Early hit a sacrifice fly to bring in Ryan Pruitt. The Bulls had a great chance to add on in the third, loading the bases with one out. But\nBrayden Sharp\ncame on and struck out Jake Kulikowski and Lance Trippel to get out of the inning.\nThe Owls (14-10, 1-1) threatened in the fifth. With one out,\nKutter-Gage Webb\nsingled to left center.\nLorenzo Rios\ndrew a walk two batters later. But they were left stranded, as\nCole Green\nstruck out to end the inning.\nThe Bulls added an insurance run in the eighth. After loading the bases with one out, Javin Relaford hit a ground ball to short. Rice got the out at second, but Relaford beat out the throw to first, allowing Trippel to score.\nRice had a chance in the ninth. With two outs, J.C. Davis and\nPaul Smith\nsingled. But\nGaret Boehm\nlined out to short to end the game.\nSenay moved to 4-0 with the win.\nRyland Urbanczyk\n(1-3) took the loss. Ethan Sutton picked up his fourth save.\nUp Next\nRice and South Florida close out the series tomorrow, Mar. 21. First pitch is scheduled for 12:05 p.m., and the game will be streamed by ESPN+.\nNotes\n*Rice is 4-2 this season in the middle game of a weekend series.\n*Rice split the first two games of a series for the first time this year.\n*\nBrayden Sharp\nrecorded a career-high 11 strikeouts in 5.0 innings of relief, tying the most strikeouts by an Owl this year.\n*It is also the first 10+ strikeout game in relief since\nDavion Hickson\nhad 10 against Charlotte on May 5, 2024.\n*Kutter-Gabe Webb extended his season-long hitting streak to seven games.\n*\nGaret Boehm\nextended his on-base streak to a season-high seven games.",
